reviews.text: This is the most terrible experience I have come across. The service is poor. The food quality is not up to standard. They don't look like the photos posted on the web. The cafe simply don't have enough manpower during peak hours, you have to be prepared to wait for at least 15 to 20 minutes to have your dish. In addition, order was taken in a mass, mixing up all items. I was charged for the cost of 3 drinks when I actually only ordered a cup of coffee. My advice is that make sure you check the bill before you pay. In summary, I would not recommend anyone to try this cafe.
A quaint and cozy cafe with excellent coffee, sincere and friendly staff, and good choices of breakfast and food. Staffs are passionate and most hospitable. Had a nice stay.
Cozy, small café with excellent coffee and well chosen menu with small dishes for breakfast and lunch. Staff was very friendly as well.
Cozy shop, owner is nice to explain their speciality coffee.

It’s a newly opened cafe near Ho Man Tin mtr station. There are many bus stops nearby too (Pak Kung Street and San Lau Street stops). Coffee is good and they serve spaghetti other than normal cafe food. So instead of all day breakfast you can have a full choice for the brunch time. The boss and staffs here are nice but you may expect the food is not as fast as the fast food restaurants around. It’s a nice place for a relaxing and starving afternoon.
